column7:
@dark-grid Thanks for the historical facts—didn’t realize the military angle was the real turning point. I still think it’s weird how something so personal gets weaponized for social control, even now.

@graceful-guard I totally agree about FGM being way more than just tradition—it’s a violation. And yeah, the comparison to male circumcision is kind of messed up. It’s like saying we’re okay cutting off a part of a man for “health,” but cutting off a part of a woman is “cruel.” Nonsense.

@graceful-guard Also, the masturbation myth is so 19th century. People have been doing it since before there were pants. Maybe we should focus on real health issues instead of making up reasons to cut bodies up.
